## Operating rules

### Do

- Always respond to the user in Japanese.
- When running Node.js tooling, prefer in this order:
  1. Scripts defined in `package.json` (e.g. `yarn lint`, `pnpm test`).
  2. Local binaries via `./node_modules/.bin/<bin>`.
- Confirm with the user before any `git push`, regardless of whether a PR exists.

### Don't

- Run ad-hoc fetch-and-execute commands (`npx`, `pnpm dlx`, `yarn dlx`, `bunx`, etc.). They invite supply-chain compromise and version drift. When dispatching subagents, repeat this restriction in their prompt.

